# Known exceptions for `pnpm run check:links` (consumed by
# `scripts/check-links.js --allowlist=...`).
#
# Format: `<file>:<line>:<href>` per line. `#` comments and blank
# lines are ignored. Each entry MUST match the printed report
# verbatim (file path relative to repo root, 1-based line number,
# href as it appeared in the source/dist).
#
# Add entries here when an issue cannot be fixed at the source —
# typically: doc pages that reference EN-only siblings from JA, or
# absolute hrefs that point at runtime-generated routes with no
# MDX file.
#
# When ANY of these stops being a known exception (e.g. someone
# writes the missing JA mirror page), DELETE the entry — the
# strict gate then surfaces real regressions in the same category.
#
# ----- Broken Links in Built HTML (1 entry) -------------------------
#
# The EN docs/claude/index.mdx (generated: true) uses <CategoryNav categories={["claude-md"]} />
# which emits a nav card to /ja/docs/claude-md/ when rendered under the JA locale.
# There is no JA claude-md content (claude-resources generates EN-only pages;
# generated: true pages are exempt from bilingual mirroring per CLAUDE.md).
# The JA /docs/claude/ page is served via i18n fallback from the EN page, so
# the CategoryNav still fires with the JA prefix. This is a known structural
# limitation of the generated/i18n interaction — not a fixable broken link.
# Same root cause for claude-skills: the generated EN claude landing also lists
# claude-skills, which has no JA mirror and fires under the JA i18n fallback.
